race.comment: GOOD LORDY ME (1) has had a few chances but does look well placed to get the job done here. He's placed in his past four, coming back slightly in trip having been run down late at Mornington and Colac. This trip looks ideal for him and he maps for every chance. DURNESS (9) ran well fresh at Mornington over 1600m when getting home late into fourth. Fitter now with the extra distance to suit, she'll be hard to hold out. ZINOVATION (5) resumes for his second campaign. He showed ability last time in with three minor placings, getting out over more ground before a break. This trip suits fresh. PETE THE PROPHET (3) appreciated a rise to 1610m third up and put in a career best. He can continue to progress.
